Count 2 - Possess Narcotic Drugs - Guilty plea.   Convicted.   State moves to dismiss and read in count 1, possess narcotic drugs and count 3, possess THC.   Motion granted.   
Sentence is withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for eighteen (18) months.   Conditions of probation are:
1) Obtain High School Diploma or HSED/GED; 
2) AODA assessment and follow through; 
3) Maintain absolute sobriety; 
4) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
5) Use only one doctor and only one pharmacy unless approved by the agent; 
6) Pay costs of action; 
7) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC; 
8) Submit DNA sample and pay surcharge.   
Minutes.
